HEADWORD: Cancrinite
<hw>Can"cri*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
Count <ets>Cancrin</ets>, a minister of finance in Russia.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral occurring in hexagonal crystals, also
massive, generally of a yellow color, containing silica, alumina, lime,
soda, and carbon dioxide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cancroid</ent>⟦br⟧
